textRegions.text: Neon extracts thumbnails that make users click.
Publishers need to increase the likelihood that users will click to watch their videos.
Little attention has been paid to the main touchpoint between the publisher and the viewer.
Publishers want to keep users on their site for longer consuming more content.
Neon extracts the best thumbnails for the audience publishers want to reach.
Our science-based approach to thumbnail selection results in better click through rates.
Neon takes a stream of video and sells thumbnail recommendations, targeted to users.
In June 2012, internet users clicked on 33 billion video thumbnails.
How do companies get users to watch more video?
